code:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column=['u', 'v'], ax=ax)
    plt.title("What is the range of values for u and v?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['u', 'v'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.heatmap(data.corr(), annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', vmin=-1, vmax=1)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between u and v?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='u')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
